value.value: Antecedente de cirugía de bypass gástrico
History of having received gastric bypass surgery. This is a procedure that reduces the functional volume of the stomach and is used to treat morbid obesity.
Provocado por compuestos orgánicos volátiles.

Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to volatile organic compounds (VOCs), which comprise various organic chemicals which are released as gases from different liquids or solids.

definition.value: VOCs are present in different household, industrial or commercial and products, but their accumulation in air and water has primarily gained attention. Among VOCs, trichloroethylene and vinyl chloride are the most toxic and carcinogenic compounds.

value.value: Antecdente de radioterapia

definition.value: A medical history of having undergone radiation therapy, which is a treatment that uses ionizing radiation for purposes such as the control the growth of malignant cells in cancer treatment.

value.value: Ausencia de emisiones otoacústicas.
Failure to record otoacoustic emissions (OAE), i.e., sounds generated from the cochlea in response to an acoustic stimulus and transmitted across the middle ear to the external ear canal.
Membrana timpánica engrosada

The tympanic membrane (eardrum, myringa) is a thin, semitransparent, oval membrane, approximately 1 cm in diameter, that separates the external acoustic meatus from the tympanic cavity. Thickening refers to an increase of the dimension across the membrane.

definition.value: See Figure 2 of PMID:23673509.

value.value: Lipoma del filum terminal
Filum terminale lipomas (FTLs) are a type of lumbosacral lipoma in which the fat is entirely within the filum terminale and separate from the conus medullaris.

definition.value: Filum terminale lipomas (FTL) are occasionally associated with tethered cord syndrome, and some authors have advocated for prophylactic sectioning of the filum terminale when an FTL is identified. With the increasing use of MRI, FTLs have been identified more frequently in asymptomatic individuals.

value.value: Relación baja de tetrahidrocortisol (THF) más 5-alfa-THF/tetrahidrocortisona (THE)
The relative concentration of tetrahydrocortisol plus 5-alpha-tetrahydrocortisol relative to that of tetrahydrocortisone is below the lower limit of normal.

definition.value: Antibodies against SLA/LP are now considered as being highly specificmarkers for auto-immune hepatitis type 1.

Positividad de anticuerpos antiespermáticos
The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against sperm antigens.
Disminución de la concentración de ficolina 3 en sangre
Concentration of ficolin 3 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.
Morfología anormal de la vesícula seminal

A structural abnormality of the seminal vesicle. The seminal vesicles are a pair of glands that also include the prostate gland and the bulbourethral glands and are located in the pelvis superior to the rectum, inferior to the fundus of the bladder and posterior to the prostate. The seminal vesicles contribute around 70% of the fluid that will eventually become semen.
Quiste de vesícula seminal
A cyst (sac-like mass that may contain serous liquid or semisolid material) caused by distention of the seminal vesicle due to atresia of the ejaculatory duct.

definition.value: Congenital seminal vesical cysts are caused by altered development of the mesonephric (Wolffian) duct. They are often associated with abnormal development of other ipsilateral mesonephric derivatives, such as vas deferens, kidney, and ureter.

value.value: Exposición al polvo de sílice
History of exposure to respirable crystalline silica (SiO2).

definition.value: Silicosis is a well known consequence of silica dust exposure, and exposure has also been associated with the risk of lung cancer, pulmonary tuberculosis, and other airway diseases.

value.value: Anticuerpos positivos anti-osteoprotegerina
The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against osteoprotegerin.
Antecedentes de adrenalectomía
A past medical history of having had a surgical procedure to remove the adrenal glands.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Elevated mitochondrial citrate synthase synthase activity

label.value: Elevated mitochondrial citrate synthase synthase activity

value.value: Activity of the enzyme mitochondrial citrate synthase (EC:2.3.3.1) in muscle tissue is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: Citrate synthase (CS) activity is a validated biomarker for mitochondrial density in skeletal muscle. CS activity is also used as a biochemical marker of the skeletal muscle oxidative adaptation to a training intervention, and a relationship between changes in whole body aerobic capacity and changes in CS activity is often assumed.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la lactato deshidrogenasa muscular.

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme lactate dehdrogenase (LHD; 1.1.1.27) in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. LDH catalyzes the conversion of pyruvate to lactate and back, as it converts NAD+ to NADH and back.

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la fosfoglicerato mutasa muscular.

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme Phosphoglycerate mutase (PGM) in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. PGM is an enzyme that catalyzes step 8 of glycolysis (EC 5.4.2.11).

value.value: Disminución de la actividad de la fosforilasa quinasa muscular.
Activity of the enzyme muscle phosphorylase kinase (PhK) in muscle tissue below the lower limit of normal.

definition.value: The enzyme PhK comprises four copies each of four subunits (alpha, beta, gamma, and delta).

Eritrocitos en el líquido cefalorraquídeo
The presence of red blood cells (RBCs) in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). The CSF normally does not contain RBCs (erythrocytes).

definition.value: Erythrocytes may be seen in CSF following a traumatic lumbar tap, but in such cases RBC counts typically decrease in sequential samples. Penetration of blood into the subarachnoid space and/or CSF may be due to trauma, a ruptured aneurysm, intracerebral hemorrhage, or in connection with a tumor.

Masa faríngea

definition.value: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to the pharynx (i.e., the throat, the space that connects the nose and mouth to the larynx and esophagus). The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

value.value: Prueba positiva para sangre oculta en materia fecal
The presence of hidden (occult) blood in the stool.

definition.value: This test is commonly used for colorectal cancer screening. Blood in stool may be a sign of hemorrhoids, colorectal cancer, or another condition.

value.value: Defecación dolorosa

definition.value: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort that occurs when passing stool.

label.value: Recent history of caustic substance ingestion

definition.value: Medical history of a recent ingestion of a caustic substance, i.e., a highly acidic or alkaline chemicals that can cause severe burns to the mouth and digestive tract when swallowed.

value.value: Retraso en la eliminación del meconio
Failure to pass meconium (the first stool following birth) in the first 48 hours of life.

definition.value: Failure to pass meconium combined with progressive abdominal distention, refusal to feed and vomiting of bilious intestinal contents are the classic clinical signs of intestinal obstruction in neonates. The first stool is passed within 24 hours of birth in 99 percent of healthy full-term infants and within 48 hours in all healthy full-term infants.

value.value: Segundo ruido cardíaco único

The second sound can remain single throughout the respiratory cycle due to either absence of one component or to synchronous occurrence of the two components. Since the pulmonary vascular impedance increases with age, many normal patients over age 50 have a single S2 or at most a narrow physiologic split on inspiration because P2 occurs early. A single second sound, however, is usually due to inability to auscultate a relatively soft pulmonic component. Such inability is rare in healthy infants, children, and young adults and is uncommon even in older persons under good auscultatory conditions using a rigid stethoscopic diaphragm.
Aumento del gradiente de presión transvalvular aórtica

Válvula cardíaca protésica

label.value: Failure to increase oxygen saturation on hyperoxia test

value.value: Fallo en el incremento de la saturación de oxígeno en la prueba de hiperoxia

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Failure to increase oxygen saturation on hyperoxia test

value.value: Hyperoxia test is the initial method to distinguish critical congenital heart disease (CCHD) from pulmonary disease. The test consists in measuring an arterial blood gas at room air and 100% inspired oxygen after 10 minutes. Neonates with congenital heart disease are usually not able to increase PaO2 above 100 mm Hg during 100% oxygen administration. In patients with pulmonary disease, PaO2 generally increased greater than or equal to 100 mm Hg with 100% oxygen as ventilation-perfusion discrepancies are overcome. A positive result indicates the cardiac origin and further cardiac workup is indicated to rule out CCHD.
